# Modal Layout Redesign Plan

The objective is to redesign the "New Lot Registration" modal to improve usability. The current single-column layout is too long. We will implement a responsive 2-column grid layout.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> I will switch to a **horizontal 2-column layout**. The form will be wider, but much shorter vertically, reducing the need to scroll.

## Proposed Changes

### CSS Changes ([style.css](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/style.css))
#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/style.css)
- Increase `.modal-content` max-width to allow side-by-side columns (e.g., `800px` or `900px`).
- Create a `.form-grid-layout` class using `display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;`.
- Use media queries to revert to single column on mobile.

### HTML Structure ([index.html](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/index.html))
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/tiesm/.gemini/antigravity/index.html)
- Wrap the form content in a wrapper div with the new grid class.
- **Left Column**:
    - Basic Info (Lot ID)
    - Lot Type (Ship/Dump)
    - Company & Unit Name (Ship Name/Car Number)
    - Capacity/Crew Info
    - Plant Name
- **Right Column**:
    - Location Info (Current Location, Destination)
    - Status & Soil Type
    - Documents & Notes
- **Full Width Bottom**:
    - Map Settings (Port Info) - keep this at the bottom but maybe in a collapsed/compact row.
    - Action Buttons.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Open Modal**: Click "New Lot Addition" (`+ 新規ロット追加`).
2.  **Check Layout**:
    - Verify the modal is wider.
    - Verify fields are split into two logical columns.
    - Check that "Ship" vs "Dump" toggle still correctly shows/hides the relevant specific fields without breaking the grid.
3.  **Responsive Check**: (Optional) Resize window to see if it wraps correctly (though user is on desktop).
